sql:
SELECT *
FROM route_stops
WHERE route_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- 'vibrant arteries of the city' refers to active bus routes;
- 'pulsating with life' signifies that the bus routes and stops are marked as active (is_active = 1);
- 'paths and destinations' refer to the route names and directions;
- 'stations where they pause' refer to the stops that the routes serve.

- "landmarks" refers to bus stops;
- "travelers" refers to the passengers of the bus routes;
- "paths" refer to bus routes;
- "entrances" refer to bus stops that have recorded arrival times (actual_arrival is not null).

sql:
SELECT route_id, AVG(delay) AS average_delay
FROM route_stops
GROUP BY route_id;

SELECT route_id, AVG(dwell_time) AS Average_Dwell_Time
FROM route_stops
GROUP BY route_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Bustling intersections' metaphorically refers to active bus stops;
- 'Frequented by vehicles lingering more than a moment' implies an average dwell time greater than 5;
- 'Often captured under the watchful eye of traffic surveillance' indicates traffic conditions recorded more than twice.

- 'Halfway point' in the context of the route refers to stop_sequence > 20, implying that the route has at least 40 stops since we consider the sequence to be approximately half way;
- 'Quick stops' are those where the dwell time is less than 60 seconds, indicating a brief stay at the stop;
- 'Cumulative position' indicates the cumulative distribution of stops in the sequence.
